      • initEngine

        public static void initEngine(java.lang.String pluginsRootDirectory,
              java.lang.String defaultPropertiesFile,
              java.lang.String logHost)
        Clover.ETL engine initialization. Should be called only once.
        Parameters:
        pluginsRootDirectory - directory path, where plugins specification is located (can be null, then is used constant from Defaults.DEFAULT_PLUGINS_DIRECTORY)
        defaultPropertiesFile - file with external definition of default values usually stored in defaultProperties
        password - password for encrypting some hidden part of graphs
        i.e. connections password can be encrypted
        can be null

      • initEngine

        public static void initEngine(java.net.URL[] pluginsUrls,
              java.lang.String defaultPropertiesFile,
              java.lang.String logHost)
        Clover.ETL engine initialization. Should be called only once.
        Parameters:
        pluginsUrls - locations of all individual engine plugins
        defaultPropertiesFile - file with external definition of default values usually stored in defaultProperties
        password - password for encrypting some hidden part of graphs
        i.e. connections password can be encrypted
        can be null

      • forceActivateAllPlugins

        public static void forceActivateAllPlugins()
        This method forces engine to activate all plugins at once. For engine initialization it is not necessary to call this method, lazy initialization is perfect for most usage of clover engine. This functionality is now used for example by clover GUI.
